       METROBANK
       
       1. Effective to use
       -The machine is effective to use in certain aspects as withdrawing is of great ease with the machine. Balance inquiry seeking with this machine is also fast and reliable as after transaction the database is automatically updated not like other ATMs. 

       2. Efficient to use
       -The machine offers its users the capability to check their account balances, deposit and withdraw money as soon as possible. ATMs rarely have maintenance check-ups and it is always efficient in handing out money to the users.
       
       3. Safe to use (safety)
       -While entering your pin in this machine, you are automatically eased and feel the safety because of the cover bridge on your hands while you are entering your pin code. The machine also offers a security camera to record every movement of the user and protect him/her from certain danger like holdups.


       4. Having good utility (utility)
       -The machine has a good utility. This is so because it has many functions that allow the user to pay with those other services. A good example of this is the bills paying of certain cable and internet bills. It is also a 3-in-1 account because it allows you to select within Checking, Savings or Credit account.

       5. Easy to learn (learnability)
       -The interface is simple and easy to navigate to. The machine uses voice-over to aid users on what to do on a step-by-step process. It also has directional arrows for the user to know what buttons to press.

       6. Easy to remember how to use (memorability)
       -Users will not find a hard time remembering how to use the ATM because the interface is consistent on all the transactions. The design is also the same as the different ATMs. The way it is easy to remember to use is just of the pressing of the buttons.

       QUESTIONS






        Sterling Bank of Asia

       1. Effective to use (effectiveness)
       -Sterling’s ATM can do an ATM’s basic functions (withrawal and balance inquiry).
       - It also provides deposit and payment function for different companies, groups and agencies.

       2. Efficient to use (efficiency)
       - The card can be inserted  and retrieved fluidly.
       -It shows important information that should be known specially by the users on the screen.
       -Receipts are available.
       -It has cash inside to give during withdrawals. 

       3. Safe to use (safety)
       - The light and colors could easily damage the eyes when used for more than around a minute.
       -The ATM  isn’t guarded well and its location is too public for a withdrawal machine..

       4. Having good utility (utility)
       -The buttons at the sides of the monitor serve their function well as they’re easy  to understand and use by the users with low computer literacy.
       -It provides bank account information that are important/critical for the users if left unknown such as account balances.

       5. Easy to learn (learnability)
       -The buttons and keypads are easy to learn, although it might take some time for the user to learn all the ropes around all the ATM’s services offered.
       -Basic functions are specially made easy to control for users.

       6. Easy to remember how to use (memorability)
       -With only a few buttons, one could easily remember what to push and type. If forgotten, the screen always guides you step-by-step.
       -The steps are easy to follow and memorize as there are patterns to be spotted when using the machine. (ie. Insert card, pick service, wait for the service, get card... etc. Different ATM’s have different sequences for the functions.)

